# 5dgai_capstone / QuantLab — read-me-first orientation

Capstone for the Google/Kaggle 5-Day GenAI: AI Agents Intensive. A research-grade algo-trading
harness (deterministic trend-following + mean-reversion, one honest backtest) + a multi-agent
market-intelligence layer that **proposes** strategy-param changes for human approval only.
**No real money. Sentiment never places/sizes a trade. LLMs are nowhere in the order path.**
Graded on agent craft → the intelligence layer (Increment C) is the centerpiece.

## Get oriented
1. `docs/specs/` — the decomposition + per-increment specs (start with the decomposition doc).
2. README.md — what/why, success definition, standing caveats.
3. This file — conventions + hard rules.

## Build order (capstone-first, interface-anchored)
A scaffold+config-interface → B honest thin core (data/indicators/strategies/min backtest+report)
→ **C ★ multi-agent intelligence layer (the graded centerpiece)** → D backfill (validation, screen,
Alpaca paper). The `tunable:` block in configs/base.yaml is the FROZEN INTERFACE the ParamProposal
targets — bounds enforced in `config.validate_proposal`, one place, in code.

## Hard rules (non-negotiable)
- **Never commit to `main`** (kaggle_projects repo protocol) — work on `milind_5dgai_capstone`.
- Secrets only in `.env` (gitignored). Alpaca = PAPER endpoint only (adapter hard-fails otherwise).
- **No trade-capable MCP / live-order tools in the dev (Claude Code) session** — injection hygiene.
- Pure core: no network / broker / `datetime.now()` in config/manifest/indicators/strategies/
  portfolio. Side effects live in adapters. Enforced by `tests/test_import_purity.py`.
- Honest measurement > pretty equity curve. "Doesn't beat SPY" cleanly shown = success.
- Swap-in seams (owner learning goal): `LLMClient`/`DataProvider`/`Broker` are protocols so
  Gemini/Alpaca/(future Rust/Robinhood) impls are ~1-file adapters.

## Env
`uv venv --python 3.11 .venv` then `uv pip install -e ".[dev]" --python .venv`.
`.venv/bin/quantlab ...` is the CLI. `uv run pytest` / `ruff check src tests` before every commit.
